The paper deals with sensor censoring for distributed sparse signal recovery in wireless sensor networks, which involves compressive sensing and signal processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing, including signal processing and compressive sensing. The paper also involves system-level considerations such as energy efficiency and communication cost, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of wireless sensor networks and communication protocols suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a modified l_1-minimization algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques and suggests the category cs.MM (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves performance analysis and simulation, which suggests the category cs.LG (Learning).
